Glad to see peaceful action against racism and intolerance. #StandUpFG

(3/4) As soon as I got back to D.C., I urged my colleagues to do more to address the problems holding back #WorkingFamilies.
(2/4) In Oregon this week, I heard moving stories from families, students, and experts about the many obstacles #WorkingFamilies face.
(1/4) Our economy will be stronger & our families will be healthier when we make policies that work FOR #WorkingFamilies not against them.
Our 21st century economy needs educated, innovative workforce to create & fill jobs.
Heading to @PortlandCC Rock Creek w/ @repbobbyscott to discuss college affordability and career readiness
Together, @repbobbyscott and I worked to pass #ESSA, #OAA, and stood up to attacks on @NLRB.

Excited to show @repbobbyscott some of OR's innovative solutions to challenges faced by working families #orpol
#WhatMomsNeed is what's good for economy too. Working families struggling to make ends meet need #paidleave, #equalpay, & #ChildCareNow
I've led the call in Congress for better access to high-quality, affordable #ChildCareNow for working families.
It’s #smallbusinessweek, so we stopped in @coffeecottage today for a delicious cup of tea.  Thank you! #DreamSmallBiz
Happy Birthday @RonWyden!
It’s time for Congress to bring mental health out of the shadows & make long term investments in care. #MHM2016
OR took steps to help working families make ends meet, it's time for Congress to do the same and #RaisetheWage!

We need to #EndDebtTrap! @RepCummings & I introduced SAFE Lending Act to crack down on predatory payday lending abuses & protect consumers

Congrats @JACKOHMAN and @kathrynschulz for winning a 2016 @PulitzerPrize!
#NotOneMore parent should have to lose a child to gun violence. Congress must act. #HonorWithAction
Pleased #SCOTUS upheld public employees right to work together for better wages, benefits. #WorkTogether #Friedrichs

We will not give in to anti-LGBT bullying. @WallyBrewster is a great public servant, I'm proud he represents USA in DR, and #imwithwally

Horrific reports out of #Brussels and more senseless loss of life. We stand with Belgium & those affected by terrorism around the world.

Good luck tonight and all season @TimbersFC #RCTID

Strengthening nutrition programs can help break the cycle of poverty. #NationalNutritionMonth
Tonight @ 6:30, I'll be on @KGWStraightTalk to discuss important issues facing Oregon and the nation. Tune in.
As a mom, I know #paidleave is important to working families. On #FLMA23, I'm working to make it a reality for all American families.
Oregon's @OHSUKnight Cancer Institute is a world leader in transforming how we detect and treat cancer. #WorldCancerDay
Good news from the House; we passed bipartisan, commonsense #housing bill to help low-income families & veterans access affordable housing.
On #GroundhogDay, House taking 12th vote to undermine women’s access to health care.
2015 was warmest year in US, OR. Growing clean energy economy will create jobs, reduce carbon pollution, & #ActOnClimate

Disappointing that the House started the new year by voting to repeal ACA & defund Planned Parenthood. #StandWithPP

May this festival of lights remind us all of the importance of religious tolerance. Happy Hanukkah!
Who will win #MLSCup? @repblumenauer & I bet pinot & @saltandstraw that @TimbersFC will topple #CrewSC! #OnwardRoseCity #RCTID
Proud to vote for #ESEA bill to strengthen public education, including my provisions to eliminate unnecessary testing and encourage #STEAM
My thoughts are with those in #SanBernardino. Enough is enough. We must do more to keep our communities safe and prevent gun violence.

Wishing you and your families a happy, peaceful #Thanksgiving!
One step closer to replacing No Child Left Behind with policies that work. Thrilled that provisions on #STEAM & less testing included.
Happy #AmericanEducationWeek! Thanks to all the educators who work tirelessly to instill a love of learning in students. #AEW2015

I hope #SCOTUS sees how the @WholeWomans case could set women's heath care back generations. #StoptheSham

Thank you, Pres. Obama, for rejecting the risky #KeystoneXL pipeline. Oregonians appreciate your leadership.
Get well soon, @RepPeterDeFazio!
Since 2014, the US has had the largest growth in apprenticeships in nearly a decade. #ApprenticeshipWorks #NAW2015
#NationalVeteransSmallBusinessWeek is a great way to recognize veteran biz owners like Dave Bax @EcoBinary. #MyVetBiz
#SocialSecurity provides retirees with a foundation of economic security. Let’s protect it for current & future recipients.
37 years ago this week the Pregnancy Discrimination Act passed - but we must do more for women who are #PregnantAtWork

I'm supporting the #WorkingFamilies Agenda to raise the federal minimum wage & pass paid family leave, affordable child care, and equal pay

Today I called for an immediate vote to #SaveLWCF. Oregonians care deeply about safeguarding our parks and forests for future generations.
Thrilled to see Portland General Electric, Nike, & Iberdrola among the 81 businesses that signed the Act on Climate Pledge #ActOnClimate

Horrified by news reports about the shooting at Umpqua CC. My thoughts are with the community, and friends and family of those affected.
On the House floor waiting for the Pope's historic address to Congress!
We should be encouraging more creativity and innovation from our students.  #IStandWithAhmed
Thanks @POTUS for taking action to provide sick leave for federal contractors. Congress should pass the Healthy Families Act. #LeadOnLeave

About to kick off our STEAM briefing w/@YoungAudiences_ and our new #STEAM cochair @RepStefanik

Honored to support Congressional Gold Medal award to those who marched for civil rights #Selma

I just signed a petition to #renewUI. We must continue to assist the #2million Americans who rely on these benefits.
Proud of my OR U.S. Senate colleagues who helped bring attention to the serious issue of climate change #Up4Climate.

The world has lost a champion for democracy, peace & equality. May Nelson Mandela find in death the peace he fought for during his life.

Great discussions at my town hall meetings in Beaverton and Banks today!

House passed bill linking govt funding to delay of health care law. How disappointing. We need to work together for the good of the country.
Just voted against legislation that defunds important health care reform,  plays politics with our economy, and risks a government shutdown.
Just voted against $39 billion in cuts to the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP). Cut poverty, not nutrition assistance.

The President is right. Improving our schools and making college more affordable are both crucial to rebuilding a strong middle-class.
Thanks to @LuisGutierrez for his important insights on Comprehensive Immigration Reform. You’re always welcome in Oregon!
#SCOTUS Voting Rights Act opinion is a major setback. Congress must quickly consider new sec 4 to restore voting rights protections.

I’m working to stop student loan interest rates from doubling. Just signed a petition for an up or down vote on Student Loan Relief Act!
Just attended roundtable and toured Scoggins Dam with @SenJeffMerkley. I’m looking for ways to help fund needed seismic upgrades.
Congratulations to Montclair Elementary Principal Verna Bailey on well-deserved retirement after 39 years of dedication to our community.
Thanks 2 Dr. Phil Mote of  Oregon's CCRI 4 meeting today. Atmospheric CO2 now 400ppm. Now is the time for action.
Proud to vote for the Homes for Heroes Act of 2013 to strengthen efforts to combat homelessness among veterans.
Celebrating National Nurses Week and  the essential contributions of nurses to our health care system!
Miss Dorrian from Northville High taught me to love reading, writing, and poetry. #TeacherAppreciationDay  #thankateacher
Thanks to @servicewomen action network for the visit. Congress must do more to stop military sexual violence. #TruthandJustice #tealribbon
Had a great meeting today with Mayor Jerry Willey and representatives of the Hillsboro business and education communities.
Our thoughts and prayers go out to the victims of the horrible and senseless act of violence in Boston.
I've signed a petition to demand an up or down vote on the #PaycheckFairnessAct. It’s time for equal pay for equal work!
Pass the  #paycheckfairnessact - women in the Portland Metro Area earn 79 cents for every dollar paid to men.  #TalkPay #equalpayday
Two key takeaways from Labor Town Hall w/ @RepSchrader – 1. #EndtheSequester 2. Stop the #RyanBudget.
Met with the STEM Employer Coalition today. More work to be done on STEM and STEAM initiatives at federal level.
Great things happening in Washington County! Great State of the County address from  County Chair Andy Duyck.
Join me tonight for screening of @STUCK2013 documentary and discussion on international adoption. 7pm at Portland’s Cinema 21.
It was an honor to speak at the Lewis & Clark Law School's Joyce Ann Harpole Awards reception. Congrats to this year’s winners.
Just toured Bimbo Bakeries USA in Beaverton w/ @BCTGM Local 114 reps. Strong union workforce, great company.
I had my fist two Town Hall meetings in Seaside and Warrenton, and I'll be doing six more soon. Hope to see you there!
Join me for a Town Hall meeting at 6pm today at the Warrenton Community Center, 225 South Main Avenue.
Join me for a Town Hall meeting in Seaside today at 10am. Seaside City Hall, 989 Broadway
Great tour of Foss Maritime Company’s Rainier Shipyard - excellent local success story!
Joined w/ @rosadelauro 2 introduce Healthy Families Act. 40 million Americans have no paid sick leave. Let’s change that. #HFAnow

Happy 101st birthday @girlscouts!

Thanks to all everyone tweeting #CutsWeCantAfford. I stand with you! #StoptheSequester
Looking forward to the Oregon Women Lawyers dinner tonight! #InternationalWomensDay
Thanks @NOAAdebris 4 #TsunamiDebris twitter chat. I’ll soon introduce two bills to help with debris removal.

Thanks to @TigardMayor John Cook for stopping by our DC office today!

Congress should #DoTheRightThing and protect middle class families and small businesses from tax increases

I applaud @whitehouse commitment to finding balanced approach to resolving fiscal cliff issue. #orpol
Looking forward to hearing about job growth in Oregon’s defense and security industry sector at the PNDC annual meeting tonight @nwdefense

text: The tragic shooting in Wisconsin deeply saddens me. My thoughts & prayers are with the families & victims of this act of senseless violence.
Today I introduced bipartisan legislation that will help communities impacted by marine debris emergencies get federal assistance.
Congrats/good luck to #OR1 Olympian @marielzagunis -- #TeamUSA's flag bearer at tonight's opening ceremonies!
Sally Ride was a pioneer in every sense of the word. May she rest in peace.
2 years ago (June 21) #DoddFrank was enacted, putting in place critical financial reforms and consumer protections
Sending thoughts and prayers to victims of senseless violence and their families in Aurora, Colorado.
Today I voted against the Defense Appropriations bill because it reflects the wrong priorities for Americans.
Congrats to @PDXArtMuseum on being selected to participate in the @StateDept’s highly competitive Museums Connect program w @museo_sancarlos
I'm on @KGWStraightTalk with @LauralPorter tonight at 6:30 on @KGWNews Channel 8. Hope you can tune in.
Mr. @SpeakerBoehner. Fair elections demand transparency. Please bring #DISCLOSE to the floor.

Great conversation about economic growth with #Oregon business leaders at @Vestas today. #economy #jobs
Today #SCOTUS rightly upheld #ACA, sustaining critical reforms to our health care system.
Thanks to @runningstartDC for inviting me to speak with young women interested in politics. #YWPL2012
Congrats to @Oregonbeer craft breweries for having a record-breaking 2011. 7.5% increased production = more #jobs, stronger local economies.
